The paper proposes a practical algorithm for committee selection with diversity constraints, which is a problem commonly studied in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The algorithm is also based on the idea of using soft bounds, which is a technique often used in optimization and constraint satisfaction problems (cs.DS). The paper also mentions natural axioms, which suggests a theoretical aspect to the work, potentially placing it in the category of social and information networks (cs.SI) or computational complexity (cs.CC).
